# AutoMet API Response Conventions

## Response Shape
All endpoints must return:
```javascript
res.status(HTTP_CODE).json({
  success: true | false,
  message: "Human-readable message",
  data: { ... }  // optional
});
```

## HTTP Codes
- `200` — Success or soft failure (e.g. trip already cancelled)
- `400` — Bad request (missing/invalid fields)
- `404` — Resource not found
- `409` — Conflict (duplicate request, already processed)
- `500` — Server error

## Cancelled/Expired Messages
When trip is cancelled or expired, return messages like:
- `"Ride was cancelled by user"`
- `"Request expired or another action was taken"`
- `"Trip already processed with status X"`

Driver app uses these to dismiss the ride request UI.
